Part of the comments are about local parts of the paper and we have
taken them into account in a new version of the paper that can be
found on the publication page of the web site of the first author.

This includes:
- replacing "flavor" with a precise word ("has the structure of a cubical / augmented simplicial set")
- using passive form rather than "we" when not a contribution
- "obtained by applying imple rules characterizing iterated parametricity" -> "generated by iterating the parametricity translation for type judgements"
- incorporating section numbers in the outline
- our precise mechanization in Coq -> our mechanization
- notation \hat{delta} for the semi-simplex category: this is Greg Friedman's terminology but it is accordingly confusing, we removed
- use of square brackets rather than curly brackets for sequences
- make explicit the dimension of standard augmented semi-simplices and semi-cubes
- make explicit that there is no augmentation in semi-cubical sets
- make explicit that the nu-set functor is contravariant
- explain from where come the coherence conditions on page 4
- explain that frames are telescopes and that νsets^{<n} abbreviate telescopes

